WEBVTT

00:05.339 --> 00:07.404
[Police sirens wail]

00:07.405 --> 00:09.138
[Church bells toll]

00:09.139 --> 00:10.571
Swat Captain: Go! Secure the exits!

00:10.572 --> 00:12.072
Go! The perimeter...

00:14.139 --> 00:18.004
♪♪♪

00:18.005 --> 00:19.405
[Sirens wail]

00:24.448 --> 00:26.741
[Reading] Pete tibi signum
a Domino Deo tuo in

00:26.742 --> 00:28.808
profundum inferni sive in

00:29.060 --> 00:30.560
excelsum supra...

00:34.608 --> 00:36.142
Trudy...

00:37.342 --> 00:38.941
[Sniffles]

00:38.942 --> 00:41.441
[Hostages whimper]

00:41.442 --> 00:42.441
[Gun racks]

00:42.442 --> 00:45.174
I said don't move.
Back against the wall.

00:45.175 --> 00:46.908
- [Hostage whimpers]
- Go!

00:48.308 --> 00:51.641
[Low hum of chatter, traffic rumbles]

00:51.642 --> 00:53.042
[Footsteps clank]

00:54.875 --> 00:56.507
[Elevator dings]

00:56.508 --> 01:02.774
♪♪♪

01:02.775 --> 01:04.808
Maxine Carlson for Eric Beaumont.

01:06.342 --> 01:08.107
I don't see your name here, Ms. Carlson.

01:08.108 --> 01:09.607
What time was your appointment?

01:09.608 --> 01:11.441
That's odd. Are you sure?

01:11.442 --> 01:13.642
Ms. Carlson has no appointment.

01:16.775 --> 01:17.974
Mr. Yates.

01:17.975 --> 01:18.807
- Hi.
- Hi.

01:18.808 --> 01:19.941
Didn't you get my message.

01:19.942 --> 01:21.174
I did.

01:21.175 --> 01:22.707
Thing is, it didn't make sense.

01:22.708 --> 01:25.341
First you tell me that I'm
perfect for the job then...

01:25.342 --> 01:26.807
I don't even get an interview.

01:26.808 --> 01:28.974
Yeah, well, that's the way
it goes sometimes.

01:28.975 --> 01:30.007
Wha...

01:30.008 --> 01:31.674
Who else can I talk to about this?

01:31.675 --> 01:33.207
I actually do the vetting.

01:33.208 --> 01:34.341
You were vetted.

01:34.342 --> 01:35.641
Now you're post-vetted.

01:35.642 --> 01:38.208
What if Mr. Beaumont disagrees?

01:39.808 --> 01:42.307
Appealing to fear of a higher authority.

01:42.308 --> 01:44.474
It's a textbook tactic.

01:44.475 --> 01:46.207
Here's the thing though.

01:46.208 --> 01:49.108
We left the textbooks behind
a longtime ago.

01:50.742 --> 01:53.274
Have a good day, Ms. Carlson.

01:53.275 --> 01:54.674
Female reporter: Here's what we
know so far:

01:54.675 --> 01:57.074
A man armed and wired with explosives

01:57.075 --> 01:58.874
entered Sainte Marie Evangelican Church

01:58.875 --> 02:00.807
And took 14 hostages.

02:00.808 --> 02:03.574
Police say he is demanding
divine intervention

02:03.575 --> 02:05.474
to save his critically ill wife.

02:05.475 --> 02:07.841
An expert negotiator has been called in

02:07.842 --> 02:09.574
and police are asking the public

02:09.574 --> 02:11.907
to stay clear of the area...

02:11.908 --> 02:15.541
♪♪♪

02:15.542 --> 02:17.407
Captain: Move! Move! Move!

02:17.408 --> 02:19.242
[Heavy footsteps thud]

02:21.242 --> 02:23.574
[Door squeaks open] Move! Move! Move!

02:23.575 --> 02:25.375
Are you listening to me?

02:26.875 --> 02:28.841
You seeing this?!

02:28.842 --> 02:30.774
[Scared gasps]

02:30.775 --> 02:33.341
You save her... you save Trudy

02:33.342 --> 02:34.574
or I'll start killing them!

02:34.575 --> 02:36.142
I swear I will!

02:37.142 --> 02:38.974
I'm listening.

02:38.975 --> 02:42.442
Keep the change. Thanks.

02:43.808 --> 02:45.407
Police Officer: We have to get
these people back over there!

02:45.408 --> 02:47.941
- Excuse me. Excuse me.
- Police: Stay back please!

02:47.942 --> 02:50.175
Crisis Resolution.
I work for Eric Beaumont.

02:51.308 --> 02:53.741
[Helicopter rotors beat]

02:53.742 --> 02:55.441
[Gate opens]

02:55.442 --> 02:57.108
[Police sirens wail]

02:58.408 --> 03:00.341
[Footsteps clunk]

03:00.342 --> 03:02.107
[Low hum of chatter]

03:02.108 --> 03:07.774
♪♪♪

03:07.775 --> 03:09.442
[Helicopter rotors beat]

03:11.475 --> 03:13.407
[Elevator dings]

03:13.408 --> 03:15.542
Hold the elevator!

03:17.108 --> 03:18.741
[Elevator dings]

03:18.742 --> 03:25.841
♪♪♪

03:25.842 --> 03:27.242
[Elevator dings]

03:29.975 --> 03:32.274
[Low hum of chatter]

03:32.275 --> 03:33.374
Thank you

03:33.375 --> 03:35.975
Police: The sniper's there now.

03:38.942 --> 03:40.274
...take her for ransom.

03:40.275 --> 03:41.641
The Archbishops plane
is still in the air.

03:41.642 --> 03:43.608
We're trying to reach him.

03:45.142 --> 03:47.007
[Low hum of chatter]

03:47.008 --> 03:48.775
Captain Charloix: Expand the AO
another...

03:50.442 --> 03:52.307
Bernard: You got to listen to me Eric.

03:52.308 --> 03:54.107
He is killing my wife!

03:54.108 --> 03:56.361
Trudy was never sick a day in her life!

03:56.908 --> 03:59.542
If God kills her, I'll show Him
that I can kill too.

04:01.175 --> 04:03.041
- [Gunshot pops]
- [Hostages scream]

04:03.042 --> 04:04.707
Red team hold your position.

04:04.708 --> 04:06.007
This has gone on long enough, Eric.

04:06.008 --> 04:07.941
You want those hostages out
of there alive, Captain,

04:07.942 --> 04:09.942
let me do my job.

04:11.875 --> 04:13.141
What about the wife?

04:13.142 --> 04:14.738
Still in surgery.

04:15.442 --> 04:17.173
Window at the back.

04:17.175 --> 04:18.475
From the rooftop behind.

04:19.575 --> 04:21.541
We finally have a clear shot.

04:21.541 --> 04:23.607
How does it look for the LCC?

04:23.608 --> 04:24.941
Police Officer: Looking good captain.

04:24.942 --> 04:28.407
We need a decision, Eric.
[Sound fades out]

04:28.408 --> 04:36.408
♪♪♪

04:38.875 --> 04:42.274
[Sound fades back in]

04:42.275 --> 04:45.075
Expand the AO another 500 meters.

04:46.408 --> 04:48.441
Okay. Contact.

04:48.442 --> 04:49.674
What are you going to do?

04:49.675 --> 04:52.274
Bear with me, Captain.
Bernard, it's Eric.

04:52.275 --> 04:54.236
- [Mumbling in Latin]
- Bernard!

04:55.142 --> 04:56.374
When I get the Archbishop on the phone,

04:56.375 --> 04:57.974
What do you want me to ask him?

04:57.975 --> 05:00.041
In excelsum supra,

05:00.042 --> 05:02.674
[Continues speaking Latin]

05:02.675 --> 05:04.741
What's he saying?

05:04.742 --> 05:06.707
Something of the Lord, your God...

05:06.708 --> 05:09.008
Ask a sign.

05:10.222 --> 05:12.621
"Ask a sign of the Lord your God."

05:12.808 --> 05:14.541
Book of Isaiah...

05:14.542 --> 05:16.007
I think.

05:16.608 --> 05:18.218
Somebody's been to Sunday school.

05:18.742 --> 05:20.407
We can take the shot now.

05:20.408 --> 05:22.975
And if you miss, what happens
to those hostages?

05:26.342 --> 05:28.107
What are you doing?

05:28.108 --> 05:29.563
He wants a sign.

05:31.008 --> 05:32.341
Let's give him one.

05:32.342 --> 05:40.342
♪♪♪

05:44.242 --> 05:45.941
[Phone rings]

05:45.942 --> 05:47.741
Hi sweetie. What's up?

05:47.742 --> 05:49.907
Stephanie is inviting me for
friend's weekend at her cottage,

05:49.908 --> 05:51.641
but Mom's saying no.

05:51.642 --> 05:54.241
Well, you want something,
you've got to give something.

05:54.242 --> 05:56.441
Concessionism. I know...

05:56.442 --> 05:58.907
How about you offer to take
that math course this summer?

05:58.908 --> 06:00.974
Might as well gouge my eyes out.

06:00.975 --> 06:02.674
Make the concession.

06:02.675 --> 06:04.374
Tell her that you'll do the course

06:04.375 --> 06:06.274
Even if she still says no.

06:06.275 --> 06:08.441
Take a risk. And then you get
the weekend.

06:08.442 --> 06:10.307
Is he doing what I think he's doing?

06:10.308 --> 06:11.841
You're the best, Dad.

06:11.842 --> 06:13.307
That's my girl.

06:13.308 --> 06:14.649
Love you.

06:19.975 --> 06:21.341
[Knocks]

06:21.342 --> 06:23.308
Bernard? It's Eric.

06:26.675 --> 06:28.641
[Door creaks open]

06:28.642 --> 06:29.807
Stay away!

06:29.808 --> 06:31.074
Red team is standing by.

06:31.075 --> 06:32.174
Sniper is set.

06:32.175 --> 06:34.075
I know you're looking
for guidance, Bernard.

06:35.208 --> 06:36.713
Me too.

06:37.442 --> 06:39.174
Maybe we can help each other.

06:39.875 --> 06:41.841
[Into hidden mic] Take your
shot ten seconds on my mark...

06:41.842 --> 06:43.407
Finally.

06:43.408 --> 06:45.874
Ten seconds, on his mark.

06:45.875 --> 06:47.341
I thought he never uses violence.

06:47.342 --> 06:49.184
Who are you, by the way?

06:50.775 --> 06:52.274
I've come unarmed.

06:52.812 --> 06:55.207
Just like Jesus into the temple.

06:55.208 --> 07:00.174
♪♪♪

07:00.175 --> 07:02.207
Trudy prayed with these people, Bernard.

07:02.208 --> 07:03.949
You don't want to hurt them.

07:05.033 --> 07:06.607
I don't think you want to hurt anybody.

07:06.608 --> 07:09.208
You just... you just want
to save your wife.

07:10.575 --> 07:11.942
Stay back.

07:13.075 --> 07:14.107
[Book thuds]

07:14.108 --> 07:15.307
Hostages: [Frightened whimpers]

07:15.308 --> 07:16.375
I'll do it.

07:18.142 --> 07:20.641
[Over radio] Wait for his mark.

07:20.642 --> 07:24.408
I believed in Him my whole life.

07:26.042 --> 07:28.742
And he does this to my wife?

07:30.142 --> 07:33.142
God thinks you doubt him, Bernard.

07:34.375 --> 07:36.574
He's testing you.

07:36.575 --> 07:37.707
[Hostages whimper]

07:37.708 --> 07:39.341
[Into hidden mic] Mark.

07:39.342 --> 07:41.141
Ten...

07:41.142 --> 07:42.607
Who's Mark?

07:42.608 --> 07:43.807
Nine...

07:43.808 --> 07:46.174
- The book of Mark, Chapter 11.
- Eight...

07:46.175 --> 07:48.974
"He who does not doubt in his
heart, it will be done for him."

07:48.975 --> 07:51.274
You want God to help to you?
You need to get on your knees.

07:51.275 --> 07:53.141
And show Him that you believe.

07:53.142 --> 07:54.342
Four... Three...

07:55.842 --> 07:57.574
Do it now, Bernard.

07:57.575 --> 08:00.507
- Two... One.
- On your knees!

08:00.508 --> 08:01.541
Fire! [Gunshot pops, glass shatters]

08:01.542 --> 08:03.874
[Hostages scream]

08:03.875 --> 08:05.375
[Relieved breaths]

08:07.508 --> 08:09.275
[Hostages whimpering]

08:12.375 --> 08:13.893
It's a sign.

08:14.608 --> 08:16.474
You submitted,

08:16.475 --> 08:18.231
and God saved you.

08:19.075 --> 08:20.842
[Hostages whimpering]

08:22.075 --> 08:23.675
[Weeps]

08:25.108 --> 08:26.775
Take off the vest...

08:29.075 --> 08:30.535
I'll hold your gun.

08:31.275 --> 08:33.107
[Weeps]

08:33.107 --> 08:39.841
♪♪♪

08:39.842 --> 08:41.974
Well, I'll be damned.

08:41.975 --> 08:43.674
Tactical, move in and do a sweep.

08:43.674 --> 08:45.607
Let's get those people out of there.

08:45.608 --> 08:47.107
[Police siren wails]

08:47.108 --> 08:49.241
[Low hum of chatter]

08:49.242 --> 08:53.407
♪♪♪

08:53.408 --> 08:54.874
Good job.

08:55.326 --> 08:56.574
What's next?

08:56.575 --> 08:59.041
Insurance executive
blackmailed in Philly.

08:59.042 --> 09:00.241
Criminal past.

09:00.242 --> 09:02.108
Get Saunders on that.

09:03.175 --> 09:05.141
- What else?
- Here's something.

09:05.142 --> 09:06.274
A couple in Denver,

09:06.275 --> 09:07.941
just received a five million
ransom demand

09:07.942 --> 09:09.407
to get their son back.

09:09.408 --> 09:10.707
And?

09:10.708 --> 09:12.808
The boy disappeared eight years ago.

09:14.375 --> 09:16.107
Mr. Beaumont!

09:16.108 --> 09:18.774
My name is Maxine Carlson.

09:18.775 --> 09:20.841
I was short-listed for
a job with your company

09:20.842 --> 09:22.907
until Oliver Yates rejected me.

09:22.908 --> 09:24.607
That's what you're doing here?

09:24.608 --> 09:26.374
If Oliver rejected you,
that's the end of it.

09:26.375 --> 09:27.607
I'm sorry, Ms. Carlson.

09:27.608 --> 09:29.302
Sir, please...

09:29.875 --> 09:32.507
I just graduated summa cum
laude from Northwestern.

09:32.508 --> 09:33.974
I've had job offers from law firms,

09:33.975 --> 09:35.707
investment bankers, tech startups...

09:35.708 --> 09:37.310
Congratulations.

09:37.875 --> 09:40.241
What you just did back there,
Mr. Beaumont.

09:40.688 --> 09:43.108
That's all I've ever wanted to do.

09:44.808 --> 09:46.142
That's it?

09:47.742 --> 09:49.197
That's your pitch?

09:49.222 --> 09:57.222
♪♪♪

09:58.742 --> 10:00.242
Get in.

10:02.975 --> 10:05.741
♪♪♪

10:05.742 --> 10:07.374
Really?

10:07.375 --> 10:09.075
She knows Latin.

10:11.842 --> 10:13.341
[Doors slam]

10:13.342 --> 10:21.342
♪♪♪

10:23.000 --> 10:29.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

10:34.676 --> 10:40.910
♪♪♪

10:42.010 --> 10:43.143
[Birds chirp]

10:44.638 --> 10:47.837
I was at class. Vince was home.

10:47.897 --> 10:49.296
I stepped out to take a call

10:49.297 --> 10:51.696
Reception was always crappy
in that house.

10:51.697 --> 10:53.763
It was five minutes.
When I came back he was gone.

10:53.764 --> 10:55.930
And this was eight years ago?

10:55.931 --> 10:58.488
And you never received
any ransom demand?

10:58.489 --> 11:00.060
- _
- Nothing.

11:00.085 --> 11:02.330
Until last night when Vince got home...

11:02.331 --> 11:04.263
that photo was taped to the garage.

11:04.264 --> 11:05.830
They say it's him.

11:05.831 --> 11:07.150
It is him...

11:07.831 --> 11:09.264
He'd be 11 now.

11:10.297 --> 11:12.196
[Door opens]

11:12.197 --> 11:13.963
[Door shuts]

11:13.964 --> 11:15.530
Mr. and Mrs. Miller,

11:15.531 --> 11:16.963
This is Oliver Yates,

11:16.964 --> 11:19.263
our psychological profiler.

11:19.264 --> 11:23.363
♪♪♪

11:23.364 --> 11:25.130
Hi.

11:25.131 --> 11:27.497
I'm just gonna set up
in there, if that's okay?

11:30.131 --> 11:31.463
So how does this work?

11:31.464 --> 11:33.230
Eric does the negotiating.

11:33.231 --> 11:35.830
I deal with law enforcement and
handle security assessments.

11:35.831 --> 11:38.030
So, you're, what? A cop?

11:38.031 --> 11:39.731
I used to be.

11:41.364 --> 11:42.731
Who's she?

11:44.597 --> 11:46.897
I'm... new.

11:51.997 --> 11:53.131
[Light thuds]

11:55.397 --> 11:57.331
[Approaching footsteps]

11:58.697 --> 12:00.620
I should explain...

12:01.264 --> 12:03.331
What's to explain?

12:04.131 --> 12:08.878
You said you'd go over my head
and then you went over my head.

12:09.597 --> 12:11.363
You'll like me once you get to know me.

12:11.364 --> 12:12.863
[Locks clank]

12:12.864 --> 12:14.130
[Sighs]

12:14.131 --> 12:16.678
Yeah. That's the thing. I do know you.

12:17.553 --> 12:19.831
I know exactly who you are.

12:22.997 --> 12:24.530
Zara: It's been eight years.

12:24.531 --> 12:26.996
Any idea why the kidnappers
would only get in touch now?

12:26.997 --> 12:28.396
Vince: It was all over the press.

12:28.397 --> 12:31.096
We had a software company.
We sold it for $23 million.

12:31.097 --> 12:33.596
Right, search optimization.

12:33.597 --> 12:35.763
That was five years ago.

12:35.764 --> 12:38.896
Look, Beth got your number
from a private investigator,

12:38.897 --> 12:40.896
but... I-I still don't get it.

12:40.897 --> 12:43.396
Why do we need a negotiator?

12:43.397 --> 12:44.596
We could just call the police.

12:44.597 --> 12:46.296
Because they said "no police"...

12:46.297 --> 12:47.763
It's a good question, Mr. Miller.

12:47.764 --> 12:50.496
And the decision is yours, of course.

12:50.497 --> 12:52.730
But police priorities are split.

12:52.731 --> 12:54.496
As well as recovering
the missing person,

12:54.497 --> 12:56.496
they have to catch the kidnappers.

12:56.497 --> 12:58.863
What you just let criminals walk away?

12:58.864 --> 12:59.963
Vince!

12:59.964 --> 13:02.164
We focus on saving lives, Mr. Miller.

13:04.097 --> 13:05.764
[Phone rings]

13:08.397 --> 13:09.863
Oliver: Unknown number!

13:09.864 --> 13:11.930
It's a burner phone. Encrypted.

13:11.931 --> 13:13.997
[Phone continues to ring]

13:20.700 --> 13:22.231
Contact.

13:23.831 --> 13:25.496
Hello.

13:26.164 --> 13:27.363
Who is this?

13:27.364 --> 13:29.063
A friend of the Millers.

13:29.064 --> 13:30.930
I said no police.

13:30.931 --> 13:32.430
I'm not the police,

13:32.431 --> 13:34.663
but I am kind of curious, why now?

13:35.131 --> 13:36.996
I mean, eight years is a long time.

13:36.997 --> 13:40.030
So what? His parents
don't want him no more?

13:40.031 --> 13:41.796
I know they'd like to talk to him.

13:42.305 --> 13:43.305
No.

13:44.997 --> 13:46.296
They're gonna need some
sort form of proof

13:46.297 --> 13:47.663
that you really have him.

13:47.664 --> 13:49.296
And that he's okay.

13:49.297 --> 13:50.663
You have a picture.

13:50.664 --> 13:53.463
That's not proof. We need DNA.

13:53.464 --> 13:54.597
No.

13:55.764 --> 13:57.130
Then there's no deal.

13:57.131 --> 13:59.113
[Phone hangs up]

13:59.664 --> 14:01.696
What the hell kind of
negotiating tactic is that?

14:01.697 --> 14:03.196
Force position.

14:03.197 --> 14:05.703
Again with the textbooks.

14:06.631 --> 14:09.624
An aggressive move to impose
a view on the adverse party.

14:10.331 --> 14:12.096
Normally used in situations

14:12.097 --> 14:14.163
where the negotiator has the upper hand.

14:14.504 --> 14:15.930
We have the upper hand?

14:15.931 --> 14:17.696
You will when he calls back.

14:17.697 --> 14:20.296
Accent sounded Mediterranean,
maybe Greek.

14:20.297 --> 14:21.563
Oliver?

14:21.564 --> 14:23.596
No latency, he's not looking
for approval.

14:24.055 --> 14:25.596
He sounded calm but it forced.

14:25.597 --> 14:27.563
Maybe impulse control issues.

14:27.564 --> 14:29.296
Come on, you heard what he said.

14:29.297 --> 14:31.563
There's not even any proof
that they have a boy.

14:32.188 --> 14:34.096
Not yet.

14:34.097 --> 14:37.463
- [Spectators] Come on!
- [Clapping] Yeah!

14:37.464 --> 14:38.463
Kylie, over here.

14:38.464 --> 14:39.824
That's it! Atta boy! Looking good!

14:41.064 --> 14:42.696
Boy: Sammy come on, we're gonna be late.

14:42.697 --> 14:44.896
[Low hum of chatter]

14:44.897 --> 14:52.897
♪♪♪

14:52.964 --> 14:54.697
[Car whooshes by]

14:57.397 --> 15:00.796
- Liam, we gotta go, come on!
- Okay.

15:00.797 --> 15:02.297
[Doors click open]

15:03.297 --> 15:05.364
[Slams shut, lock clicks]

15:06.531 --> 15:10.930
♪♪♪

15:10.931 --> 15:13.796
- [Banging on window]
- Help! Help!

15:13.797 --> 15:15.664
- [Engine turns]
- Help me!

15:19.794 --> 15:26.993
♪♪♪

15:26.994 --> 15:28.961
[Approaching footsteps]

15:30.194 --> 15:32.081
Professional negotiator.

15:32.594 --> 15:34.460
Never heard that one before.

15:34.461 --> 15:36.669
Well, Most people haven't.
Until they need one.

15:36.976 --> 15:38.671
You're an expensive option.

15:39.591 --> 15:41.723
I won't ask more than you can afford.

15:41.748 --> 15:44.515
And if I don't get your
son back, you don't pay.

15:47.461 --> 15:49.181
You don't use the pool so much?

15:50.194 --> 15:51.475
Pump broke.

15:52.127 --> 15:53.826
I didn't see much point in fixing it.

15:53.827 --> 15:55.396
- Listen, Mr. Beaumont...
- Eric.

15:56.394 --> 15:58.024
I don't mean to be rude,

15:58.620 --> 16:00.086
but you gotta understand...

16:00.111 --> 16:02.013
You lost your son once.

16:02.038 --> 16:04.238
I don't imagine you wanna
go through that again.

16:07.335 --> 16:09.734
Mr. Beaumont? He's calling back!

16:09.861 --> 16:17.861
♪♪♪

16:19.437 --> 16:20.436
This is Eric.

16:20.437 --> 16:22.536
Gas station, Route 6,

16:22.537 --> 16:24.036
east of Golden.

16:24.037 --> 16:25.503
One hour.

16:27.337 --> 16:29.436
Oliver, Zara, you're holding the fort.

16:29.437 --> 16:31.537
Maxine, you're with me.

16:37.003 --> 16:41.102
♪♪♪

16:41.103 --> 16:42.537
[Door opens]

16:43.970 --> 16:45.536
[Phone game music plays]

16:45.537 --> 16:47.169
What are you doing Vlaka?!

16:47.170 --> 16:49.853
That thing have Internet, GPS.

16:49.878 --> 16:51.278
[Speaks Greek] Throw away!

16:53.437 --> 16:55.436
Get rid of minivan too!

16:55.437 --> 16:57.403
[Keys jingle]

17:00.384 --> 17:01.584
[Mumbles]

17:02.677 --> 17:04.876
[Yelling in Greek]

17:04.921 --> 17:07.253
Come on. Go! Go! Come on.

17:07.279 --> 17:08.744
[Speaks Greek]

17:12.170 --> 17:14.036
Why can't he talk?

17:14.037 --> 17:15.737
Because my brother have no tongue.

17:17.770 --> 17:19.021
Our father...

17:19.670 --> 17:21.403
He cut it out.

17:22.820 --> 17:24.454
I want to call my Mom and Dad.

17:24.537 --> 17:25.803
[Car rumbles]

17:28.002 --> 17:29.902
Why for you do that?

17:29.903 --> 17:32.502
That house, is no fun for you.

17:32.503 --> 17:35.036
They made you go to church everyday.

17:35.037 --> 17:37.636
Too much Church, no good.

17:38.040 --> 17:40.668
Plus, they lie to you your whole life.

17:41.170 --> 17:43.569
Your real parents, they're not dead.

17:43.838 --> 17:45.936
But you smart?

17:45.937 --> 17:47.837
You figure out, yeah?

17:49.476 --> 17:51.242
They're alive, right?

17:51.370 --> 17:53.336
That's why we bring you here.

17:53.337 --> 17:55.599
To help them, to get you back.

17:58.037 --> 17:59.336
And for money.

17:59.337 --> 18:01.069
[Chuckles]

18:01.070 --> 18:03.437
Smart. Smart boy.

18:05.947 --> 18:07.113
[Speaks Greek]

18:08.033 --> 18:09.999
Come here. Come here!

18:10.170 --> 18:11.603
[Light thud]

18:13.837 --> 18:18.402
♪♪♪

18:18.403 --> 18:20.403
[Thunder cracks, rain patters heavily]

18:23.370 --> 18:31.370
♪♪♪

18:34.770 --> 18:38.869
So what else should I know
about you, Ms. Carlson?

18:38.870 --> 18:41.479
Other than your impressive GPA, that is.

18:43.570 --> 18:45.802
I always wanted to do this.

18:45.803 --> 18:47.636
So you said.

18:47.637 --> 18:49.653
You didn't say why.

18:51.970 --> 18:53.699
That guy in the church.

18:54.570 --> 18:56.337
How did you know it would work?

18:58.403 --> 18:59.802
What someone wants and
what someone needs

18:59.803 --> 19:01.602
are often two different things.

19:01.603 --> 19:03.802
And that man wanted to save his wife.

19:03.803 --> 19:06.087
What he needed was his faith restored.

19:06.937 --> 19:09.003
And if you were wrong...

19:10.303 --> 19:12.669
[Rain patters]

19:12.670 --> 19:20.402
♪♪♪

19:20.403 --> 19:22.869
- Is that him?
- Yup.

19:22.870 --> 19:24.313
He's probably armed, right?

19:24.903 --> 19:26.237
Probably.

19:27.303 --> 19:28.901
But you're not?

19:30.070 --> 19:33.202
No. It's kind of hard to
build trust carrying a gun.

19:33.203 --> 19:35.202
So he could just shoot you.

19:35.203 --> 19:36.902
Yeah, he could.

19:36.903 --> 19:38.118
Stay here.

19:38.119 --> 19:40.403
[Rain patters heavily]

19:41.670 --> 19:43.302
[Door shuts]

19:43.303 --> 19:51.303
♪♪♪

19:52.703 --> 19:54.468
Do you have the proof?

19:56.487 --> 19:59.598
The proof. DNA.

20:01.237 --> 20:02.937
[Wipers whir]

20:05.303 --> 20:06.702
[Door shuts]

20:06.703 --> 20:08.399
What? You didn't hear me?

20:08.837 --> 20:10.702
We had an agreement!

20:10.703 --> 20:12.837
[Maxine screams]

20:13.729 --> 20:15.228
[Mumbled Shout]

20:15.370 --> 20:19.610
♪♪♪

20:19.635 --> 20:21.287
I'm not a cop.

20:21.312 --> 20:29.312
♪♪♪

20:33.037 --> 20:34.437
[Mumbled Shout]

20:40.962 --> 20:42.628
- [Punching thud]
- Agh!

20:46.637 --> 20:48.537
Here is your DNA

20:50.203 --> 20:51.703
You have 24 hours.

20:52.710 --> 20:54.043
[Yells in Greek]

20:55.738 --> 20:58.137
Are you okay?

21:01.637 --> 21:03.737
I told you to stay in the car.

21:07.537 --> 21:10.837
[Car doors shut and engine turns]

21:13.303 --> 21:16.636
Aren't you even curious why
I rejected her application?

21:16.637 --> 21:17.770
Not really.

21:19.137 --> 21:20.387
Why not?

21:20.870 --> 21:22.669
Because Eric knows what he's doing.

21:22.670 --> 21:26.136
You know, Eric's never gone
against my recommendation before.

21:26.137 --> 21:27.902
Not once.

21:27.903 --> 21:29.688
I think it's strange.

21:30.703 --> 21:32.803
Were you a solid hire
when Eric found you?

21:34.170 --> 21:35.653
Was I?

21:36.573 --> 21:39.939
Your loyalty is pathological.

21:39.964 --> 21:42.596
Oh do not shrink me, Oliver.

21:42.670 --> 21:44.437
You're the one who's obsessing.

21:45.803 --> 21:46.902
[Approaching footsteps]

21:46.903 --> 21:50.102
Two men, faces obscured.
Late 40s, early 50s.

21:50.103 --> 21:52.002
One of them is armed and violent.

21:52.003 --> 21:53.269
He's running the show.

21:53.270 --> 21:55.102
The other just does what he's told.

21:55.103 --> 21:57.469
He swore. Definitely Greek.

21:57.470 --> 21:58.869
How long to confirm?

21:58.870 --> 22:00.802
36 hours, if I pull a favor.

22:00.803 --> 22:02.503
He said we have 24 hours.

22:03.763 --> 22:05.095
I'll see what I can do.

22:05.120 --> 22:07.360
There was no deadline when he
left that photo last night.

22:07.537 --> 22:09.470
Suddenly he's in a hurry.

22:10.870 --> 22:12.398
Why?

22:17.137 --> 22:18.837
[Phone game music]

22:20.221 --> 22:26.920
♪♪♪

22:26.945 --> 22:28.679
[Mumbled invitation]

22:41.047 --> 22:42.212
No. No.

22:42.503 --> 22:44.096
Press this button.

22:44.624 --> 22:45.823
Scroll around here.

22:46.003 --> 22:48.836
[Approaching engine rumbles]

22:48.837 --> 22:50.477
Hold on this harder

22:50.770 --> 22:52.402
and it will shoot harder.

22:52.403 --> 22:53.690
Good. Good. Good.

22:53.715 --> 22:55.080
[Chuckles]

22:55.203 --> 22:57.002
[Door shuts]

22:57.003 --> 22:58.003
[Crow caws]

23:01.603 --> 23:03.770
[Door rattles]

23:05.970 --> 23:07.803
[Sounds from the game]

23:09.910 --> 23:12.742
Hey Vlaka, I say to throw away!

23:12.870 --> 23:14.402
[Phone thuds]

23:14.403 --> 23:16.670
[Loud stomps, glass breaks]

23:17.537 --> 23:19.469
You know what they will do to us, hm?

23:19.470 --> 23:20.869
Why don't you listen to me?

23:20.870 --> 23:22.470
[Mumbled cries]

23:24.903 --> 23:26.737
[Landing thud]

23:28.243 --> 23:30.043
[Shouting in Greek]

23:32.170 --> 23:34.136
- [Hard punch]
- Agh!

23:34.137 --> 23:35.502
[Shouting in Greek]

23:35.503 --> 23:38.136
when you don't listen to me
you see what you make me do?

23:38.137 --> 23:39.202
[Landing thud]

23:39.203 --> 23:43.236
♪♪♪

23:43.237 --> 23:45.070
[Kicking thud] Eh?

23:47.237 --> 23:48.736
[Numbers dialing]

23:48.737 --> 23:50.103
[Phone ringing]

23:51.370 --> 23:53.437
[Phone rings]

23:56.170 --> 23:57.836
This is Eric.

23:58.637 --> 24:00.236
[Whispering] He's hurting him...

24:00.237 --> 24:01.436
Jason?

24:01.437 --> 24:04.202
Who? Who's he hurting?

24:04.203 --> 24:05.636
His brother.

24:05.637 --> 24:07.803
[Punching thud]

24:09.203 --> 24:11.058
We were just playing Netbuster.

24:11.503 --> 24:13.136
Are you all right, buddy?

24:13.137 --> 24:14.803
I'm okay.

24:16.303 --> 24:18.303
- What's your name?
- Samuel.

24:20.037 --> 24:21.802
We're going to get you back.

24:21.803 --> 24:22.970
You're going to be safe.

24:24.143 --> 24:25.842
It's your fault. You don't listen.

24:26.103 --> 24:27.602
Can you tell me where you are?

24:27.603 --> 24:29.837
[Approaching footsteps crunch]

24:34.264 --> 24:42.264
♪♪♪

24:46.264 --> 24:48.030
Brave boy.

24:48.031 --> 24:49.997
He said they were brothers.

24:49.998 --> 24:52.230
He was playing a game with
one of them. Netbuster.

24:52.231 --> 24:54.397
Yeah, soccer game
for a handheld console.

24:54.398 --> 24:55.930
My kid plays it all the time.

24:55.931 --> 24:57.363
What are we missing here?

24:57.364 --> 24:59.064
Can you bring up that photo?

24:59.731 --> 25:02.198
The one they left
with the ransom demand.

25:03.764 --> 25:05.463
Underneath the windbreaker.

25:05.464 --> 25:07.263
Burgundy and white. Team colors.

25:07.264 --> 25:08.930
We find the school with those colors.

25:08.931 --> 25:10.663
We find where the boy
has been all these years.

25:10.664 --> 25:13.297
And maybe why no one's
recently reported him missing.

25:13.298 --> 25:14.598
I'm on my way.

25:15.598 --> 25:16.831
I'll come with you.

25:20.264 --> 25:23.397
It's time to start gathering
the ransom money, Mr. Miller.

25:23.398 --> 25:24.997
What? I-I'm sorry,

25:24.998 --> 25:26.230
we're not paying anything

25:26.231 --> 25:28.330
until we know for sure
that this is Jason.

25:28.331 --> 25:30.330
They have a child, don't they?

25:30.331 --> 25:31.530
I mean, even if it isn't Jason,

25:31.531 --> 25:33.630
we could still save a little boy's life!

25:33.631 --> 25:35.197
Okay, look, Beth?

25:35.198 --> 25:36.297
Okay. I've had it with this.

25:36.298 --> 25:37.530
I'm calling the cops.

25:37.531 --> 25:39.197
- No police.
- Beth!

25:39.198 --> 25:41.731
No! They said they'd kill him!

25:42.764 --> 25:43.897
[Sighs]

25:43.898 --> 25:45.730
Now, you make that call,

25:45.731 --> 25:47.964
and I will never forgive you.

25:55.364 --> 25:58.123
You need to tell your wife, Mr. Miller.

25:59.031 --> 26:00.730
Tell her what?

26:00.731 --> 26:02.497
The broken pool,

26:02.498 --> 26:04.130
the pile of credit card statements,

26:04.131 --> 26:06.264
She's going to find out soon enough.

26:12.531 --> 26:14.348
Beth...

26:17.331 --> 26:19.363
Don't you dare tell me that I am crazy,

26:19.364 --> 26:21.930
or that I'm grieving, or that
I'm holding onto a ghost.

26:21.931 --> 26:23.464
It's not that.

26:26.731 --> 26:28.195
There's no money.

26:28.698 --> 26:31.406
What... what do you mean,
there's no money?

26:32.364 --> 26:33.575
I lost it.

26:34.975 --> 26:36.208
All of it?

26:36.764 --> 26:38.205
It wasn't all at once.

26:38.831 --> 26:40.397
The more I put in, the more I lost.

26:40.398 --> 26:41.831
And before you know it...

26:43.864 --> 26:45.504
[Emotional] How could you do that?

26:46.031 --> 26:47.798
How could you do that?

26:48.831 --> 26:50.431
I lost our son...

26:54.231 --> 26:56.348
And then I lost the money...

27:00.664 --> 27:02.229
If I lose you too...

27:03.188 --> 27:04.597
I just...

27:04.598 --> 27:06.664
[Crying]

27:09.231 --> 27:10.863
[Birds chirp]

27:10.864 --> 27:18.864
♪♪♪

27:24.831 --> 27:26.563
[Footsteps crunch]

27:26.564 --> 27:33.998
♪♪♪

27:38.431 --> 27:40.297
You want to tell me something?

27:40.298 --> 27:46.131
♪♪♪

27:54.831 --> 27:56.898
[Phone rings]

28:00.664 --> 28:02.498
I know you talked to the boy.

28:03.664 --> 28:06.063
You pay or we kill him.

28:06.418 --> 28:07.731
Hold on.

28:09.231 --> 28:11.663
We need to confirm the DNA.

28:11.664 --> 28:14.397
No! No more waiting!

28:14.398 --> 28:16.398
Listen I know you've been
through a lot of trouble.

28:16.778 --> 28:18.931
We need time to get the money.

28:21.450 --> 28:22.730
Hey, my friend,

28:22.731 --> 28:24.197
Five million dollars

28:24.198 --> 28:26.397
or I send you his heart!

28:27.012 --> 28:28.212
[Hangs up]

28:29.898 --> 28:31.963
How much money can you put
together, Mr. Miller?

28:31.964 --> 28:33.863
Not anywhere near $5 million.

28:33.864 --> 28:34.955
How much?

28:34.980 --> 28:36.379
Um...

28:36.664 --> 28:38.763
well, we still have some IRAs,

28:38.764 --> 28:41.597
and a... a line of credit.

28:41.598 --> 28:43.663
M-maybe 700 thousand...

28:43.664 --> 28:44.864
Go to the bank.

28:46.498 --> 28:48.963
[Low hum of chatter]

28:48.964 --> 28:52.505
[Door open and shut]

28:52.506 --> 28:57.597
♪♪♪

28:57.598 --> 28:59.363
But the office is back this way.

28:59.364 --> 29:02.230
We waltz in there and
ask about a missing boy.

29:02.231 --> 29:03.730
What happens next?

29:03.731 --> 29:05.797
They call the cops. Right.

29:05.798 --> 29:07.630
Exactly.

29:07.631 --> 29:08.863
Ah! there it is.

29:08.864 --> 29:10.273
That's what we need.

29:12.698 --> 29:15.330
We're looking for a kid
who plays soccer,

29:15.331 --> 29:17.431
Name's Samuel.

29:20.864 --> 29:21.897
There!

29:21.898 --> 29:23.164
Back row.

29:24.298 --> 29:25.830
Brett. Samuel Brett.

29:25.831 --> 29:28.225
Samuel Brett

29:28.831 --> 29:31.563
Nope. No address listed here.

29:31.564 --> 29:33.004
Can I help you?

29:33.898 --> 29:36.198
Visitors have to sign at the office.

29:37.764 --> 29:39.678
You don't recognize this man?

29:40.398 --> 29:42.630
This is Rivaldo Messi.

29:42.631 --> 29:44.724
World's greatest soccer player.

29:45.398 --> 29:48.730
Mr. Messi's is in Denver
playing an exhibition game.

29:48.731 --> 29:51.547
And he received the sweetest
fan mail letter

29:51.548 --> 29:53.445
from a little boy here who
really wants to meet him.

29:53.469 --> 29:56.336
Tell her how moved you
were when you read it.

29:57.764 --> 30:00.549
Uh... Ola...

30:00.798 --> 30:03.398
Come on. You were in tears.

30:05.064 --> 30:08.431
Sim... sim... How you say...

30:08.964 --> 30:11.226
many tears...

30:11.698 --> 30:13.063
Who is the student?

30:13.064 --> 30:14.297
Samuel Brett.

30:14.298 --> 30:16.130
Ah yes. He's on the varsity team.

30:16.131 --> 30:18.530
Samuel is marked as absent today.

30:18.531 --> 30:20.163
Oh, that's a shame.

30:20.164 --> 30:21.797
We came all this way.

30:21.798 --> 30:23.831
- Hmmm.
- Okay, thank you.

30:27.731 --> 30:30.979
You wouldn't happen to have
his home address, would you?

30:31.398 --> 30:33.663
The Brett's house should be on the left.

30:33.664 --> 30:35.530
[Car rumbles]

30:35.531 --> 30:37.330
This is it. 34.

30:37.331 --> 30:39.279
Pretty quick on your feet back there.

30:39.698 --> 30:41.430
I say what I have to say.

30:41.431 --> 30:43.231
Yeah. Me, too. Look...

30:44.564 --> 30:46.130
Once this is all over,

30:46.131 --> 30:48.430
you know I have to tell him
who you are, right?

30:48.847 --> 30:51.230
I get why you want to be here

30:51.231 --> 30:52.375
I get it.

30:52.964 --> 30:54.961
But it's my job to protect Eric.

30:55.264 --> 30:57.130
I don't pose any threat
to Mr. Beaumont...

30:57.131 --> 30:58.924
Emotions are a threat.

30:59.331 --> 31:00.963
And let's be honest Maxine.

31:00.964 --> 31:02.802
You bring a lot of emotions.

31:03.498 --> 31:06.097
I've dealt with my mother's
death, Oliver.

31:06.098 --> 31:08.163
I appreciate that,

31:08.164 --> 31:10.894
but I can't let you anywhere near him.

31:11.698 --> 31:13.131
[Door shuts]

31:14.464 --> 31:16.631
Maxine: [Exasperated sigh]

31:18.823 --> 31:19.990
[Door slams]

31:20.564 --> 31:22.131
[Door bell rings]

31:23.631 --> 31:25.730
[Footropes thud]

31:25.731 --> 31:26.798
[Knocks]

31:27.898 --> 31:29.330
[Knocking]

31:29.331 --> 31:37.331
♪♪♪

31:41.564 --> 31:43.463
It's open.

31:43.464 --> 31:44.964
Hey!

31:48.131 --> 31:49.863
[Door creaks open]

31:49.864 --> 31:51.101
Hello?!

31:51.431 --> 31:52.978
Anybody home?

31:53.331 --> 32:01.331
♪♪♪

32:03.298 --> 32:06.097
[Footsteps thud lightly]

32:06.098 --> 32:10.997
♪♪♪

32:10.998 --> 32:12.622
Mom and Dad.

32:12.931 --> 32:15.330
They look like a couple of nice folks.

32:15.331 --> 32:18.064
So why haven't you reported him missing?

32:23.331 --> 32:25.331
[Footsteps thud lightly]

32:29.964 --> 32:31.731
Someone left in a hurry

32:32.343 --> 32:34.663
No password protection.

32:34.664 --> 32:36.898
[Keys clack]

32:38.264 --> 32:40.063
Well, they left some files behind.

32:40.064 --> 32:42.097
Could make for some interesting reading.

32:42.098 --> 32:44.798
- [Meow]
- Copy this, then we'll get out of here.

32:48.164 --> 32:50.164
[Footsteps thud lightly]

32:52.531 --> 32:57.930
♪♪♪

32:57.931 --> 32:58.997
[Door opens]

32:58.998 --> 33:00.931
[Screeching meow!]

33:08.364 --> 33:10.530
[Footsteps thud lightly]

33:10.531 --> 33:18.497
♪♪♪

33:18.498 --> 33:19.764
[Flies buzzing]

33:21.764 --> 33:28.963
♪♪♪

33:28.964 --> 33:30.430
Oliver!

33:30.431 --> 33:36.298
♪♪♪

33:39.298 --> 33:42.712
Mr. and Mrs. Brett, I presume.

33:43.813 --> 33:45.298
They killed them?

33:45.747 --> 33:47.579
It appears so.

33:47.580 --> 33:49.179
We've need to call the police!

33:49.180 --> 33:51.146
That's your decision,
Mr. and Mrs. Miller.

33:51.147 --> 33:53.846
But I would strongly
advise against that.

33:53.847 --> 33:55.179
Why?

33:55.180 --> 33:57.560
So they don't kill the boy.

34:01.880 --> 34:03.566
I don't understand.

34:04.280 --> 34:07.446
You pay a kidnapper,
he releases his victim.

34:07.447 --> 34:10.146
A killer can't afford
to leave witnesses.

34:10.147 --> 34:11.379
But by that logic,
they're going to kill him

34:11.380 --> 34:13.212
no matter what we do.

34:13.213 --> 34:14.612
They might.

34:14.612 --> 34:16.746
But I'm here to make sure
that doesn't happen.

34:16.746 --> 34:19.712
[Maxine clears her throat]
The files are up.

34:19.713 --> 34:23.045
So, the Bretts got Samuel
through an agency

34:23.047 --> 34:25.379
trafficking infants abducted in the U.S.

34:25.380 --> 34:29.312
Now The FBI almost busted
them four years ago,

34:29.313 --> 34:31.446
but some of the fencers vanished,

34:31.447 --> 34:33.045
including two brothers,

34:33.047 --> 34:35.812
involved in at least
three other abductions.

34:35.813 --> 34:37.112
I'm going to take a wild guess...

34:37.112 --> 34:39.846
Yannick and Niko Kalvos.

34:39.847 --> 34:42.179
And The Bretts didn't know
it was illegal.

34:42.179 --> 34:43.379
Oh, they knew.

34:43.380 --> 34:45.045
How do you know that?

34:45.047 --> 34:46.512
My guess is the boy discovered

34:46.513 --> 34:48.512
the Bretts weren't his real parents,

34:49.237 --> 34:53.146
he contacted the bogus agency
who alerted the kidnappers,

34:53.574 --> 34:55.679
the kidnappers panicked,
killed the Bretts,

34:55.679 --> 34:58.621
and then decided to ransom
the boy back to the Millers.

34:59.113 --> 35:01.046
DNA report's in.

35:01.047 --> 35:08.179
♪♪♪

35:08.180 --> 35:09.913
He's your son.

35:11.313 --> 35:12.413
[Phone rings]

35:13.947 --> 35:21.312
♪♪♪

35:21.313 --> 35:22.812
This is Eric.

35:22.813 --> 35:24.812
Have you confirmed the DNA?

35:24.813 --> 35:26.079
We have.

35:26.080 --> 35:26.879
Good.

35:26.880 --> 35:28.646
Now I want my money.

35:28.860 --> 35:30.646
Five million.

35:30.647 --> 35:31.946
Well, there's a problem.

35:31.947 --> 35:33.479
The Millers don't have it.

35:33.480 --> 35:35.412
[Chuckles]

35:35.413 --> 35:36.812
You're lying!

35:36.813 --> 35:38.946
I wish I was. But they're broke.

35:38.947 --> 35:40.346
Hey, hey my friend.

35:40.347 --> 35:43.079
Do you think that I won't kill him?!

35:43.516 --> 35:44.918
I know you will.

35:45.919 --> 35:47.212
Believe me, I want to give you
what you want,

35:47.213 --> 35:49.913
so we can get the boy, safe and sound.

35:51.713 --> 35:53.080
[Fire crackles]

35:56.413 --> 35:58.379
How much do they have?

35:58.380 --> 35:59.979
$700,000.

35:59.980 --> 36:01.746
That's not enough! No!

36:01.747 --> 36:03.879
I told you. Five million.

36:03.880 --> 36:06.113
We know you killed the Bretts, Yannick.

36:07.513 --> 36:09.317
What's that sound you hear?

36:11.694 --> 36:13.179
I don't hear anything.

36:13.180 --> 36:15.046
Exactly. I haven't called the police,

36:15.047 --> 36:16.646
who would be all over you by now.

36:16.647 --> 36:18.979
$700,000 and you and your
brother walk away.

36:18.980 --> 36:21.712
But you need to bring the boy to us.

36:21.713 --> 36:25.346
Do you think that
you can play with me, eh?!

36:25.347 --> 36:27.346
You think I won't track
you down? I would do it.

36:27.347 --> 36:29.012
I would do it just because.

36:29.013 --> 36:30.779
I will kill you in your sleep...

36:30.780 --> 36:32.312
JUST BECAUSE!

36:32.313 --> 36:34.312
$700,000 is all there is.

36:34.313 --> 36:37.079
If you insist on more then this
is over and we all leave.

36:37.080 --> 36:39.547
We all go home. It's over. It's done.

36:42.280 --> 36:43.880
[Fire crackles]

36:49.913 --> 36:51.779
Falcon Creek Mall.

36:51.780 --> 36:54.412
Parking structure. Top level. 1 AM.

36:54.413 --> 36:56.079
[Phone beeps off]

36:56.080 --> 36:58.280
What do we do now?

36:59.993 --> 37:01.512
Get your son back.

37:01.513 --> 37:09.079
♪♪♪

37:09.080 --> 37:11.146
[Screech to a halt]

37:11.147 --> 37:12.579
[Engine shuts off]

37:12.580 --> 37:14.713
We got company.

37:16.347 --> 37:18.679
Let's go.

37:18.680 --> 37:20.413
[Seatbelts click]

37:21.680 --> 37:23.379
[Sirens wail in the distance]

37:23.380 --> 37:24.979
[Doors shut]

37:24.980 --> 37:27.412
- [Dials phone]
- [Speaks Greek]

37:27.413 --> 37:28.813
[Door opens]

37:30.013 --> 37:31.347
[Door shuts]

37:32.447 --> 37:40.447
♪♪♪

37:48.166 --> 37:49.379
Eric.

37:49.380 --> 37:50.779
Give him the money.

37:50.780 --> 37:52.579
As soon as you give us the boy.

37:52.580 --> 37:54.546
I have the boy. He's here with me.

37:54.547 --> 37:55.713
Well, I need to see him.

37:58.980 --> 38:00.080
[Door opens]

38:01.547 --> 38:07.179
♪♪♪

38:07.180 --> 38:09.346
You okay, Samuel?

38:09.347 --> 38:11.179
You'll be all right, pal.

38:11.180 --> 38:13.212
Now you give him the money.

38:13.213 --> 38:15.180
Phone's going into the pocket.

38:18.280 --> 38:20.112
You like the boy, don't you?

38:20.113 --> 38:22.046
You played that soccer game with him.

38:22.047 --> 38:23.479
That's why you and your brother
were fighting.

38:23.480 --> 38:25.812
You don't want him to get hurt
like he hurt you.

38:25.813 --> 38:27.747
Don't look at him, look at me.

38:30.113 --> 38:32.669
He killed the Bretts, Niko.

38:34.680 --> 38:36.255
He didn't tell you, did he?

38:36.747 --> 38:38.212
He hasn't told you he's
gonna kill the boy, too.

38:38.213 --> 38:41.047
Just as soon as we give you the money.

38:44.380 --> 38:47.079
Go ahead. Take a look inside.

38:47.080 --> 38:48.479
It's all there.

38:48.480 --> 38:51.013
$700,000 just as we promised.

38:52.371 --> 38:54.371
_

38:55.880 --> 38:57.712
Now you can walk away.

38:57.713 --> 39:00.046
Or you can use that to save the boy.

39:00.047 --> 39:01.572
Niko!

39:02.180 --> 39:03.480
Listen to me.

39:04.647 --> 39:06.680
It's time to stand up to him.

39:09.247 --> 39:13.179
♪♪♪

39:13.180 --> 39:15.128
Go ahead.

39:16.113 --> 39:17.246
[Receding footsteps]

39:17.247 --> 39:25.247
♪♪♪

39:27.047 --> 39:29.012
[Yells in Greek]

39:29.013 --> 39:31.879
♪♪♪

39:31.880 --> 39:34.379
[Money rustles]

39:34.380 --> 39:39.446
♪♪♪

39:39.447 --> 39:40.713
[Mumbled Greek]

39:41.747 --> 39:43.146
Hey...

39:43.147 --> 39:44.479
[Spray hisses] Ahhhhhh!

39:44.480 --> 39:45.946
Go!

39:45.947 --> 39:48.546
[Engine roars, tires screech]

39:48.547 --> 39:51.112
[Gunshot pops]

39:51.113 --> 39:53.246
Oof! [landing thud]

39:53.247 --> 39:54.847
[Tires screech]

39:56.780 --> 39:57.779
[Punching thud]

39:57.780 --> 39:58.912
Come on!

39:58.913 --> 40:00.012
[Fighting grunts]

40:00.013 --> 40:01.712
It's okay.

40:01.713 --> 40:03.812
[Fighting grunts]

40:03.813 --> 40:05.813
[Thuds, grunts] Ahhhh!

40:07.713 --> 40:09.782
- [Forced exhale]
- [Groans]

40:12.713 --> 40:13.913
[Car rumbles]

40:15.047 --> 40:19.212
♪♪♪

40:19.213 --> 40:20.679
Jason!

40:20.680 --> 40:22.046
[Crying]

40:22.047 --> 40:24.113
I mean... Samuel.

40:26.313 --> 40:29.246
Social Worker: We're going to
need some time with your son,

40:29.247 --> 40:32.212
there's a legal process,
lots to get in order

40:32.213 --> 40:34.046
before we can get him back to you.

40:34.047 --> 40:36.146
[Siren chirps]

40:36.147 --> 40:44.147
♪♪♪

40:45.713 --> 40:47.386
You did good.

40:51.447 --> 40:53.547
Case is over.

40:55.113 --> 40:56.613
Time to tell him.

41:02.247 --> 41:04.079
[Ahem]

41:04.080 --> 41:06.079
Mr. Beaumont?

41:06.080 --> 41:08.199
There's something I should
have said up front.

41:09.013 --> 41:12.079
The reason Oliver rejected my
application is because...

41:12.080 --> 41:14.280
I know who you are, Ms. Carlson.

41:18.213 --> 41:19.779
Why didn't you say anything?

41:19.780 --> 41:21.812
I left that ball in your court.

41:21.813 --> 41:23.446
A negotiation?

41:23.447 --> 41:24.757
There you go.

41:25.591 --> 41:28.012
Oliver thought I would come
with too much emotion.

41:28.013 --> 41:29.812
Oliver may be right. He usually is.

41:29.813 --> 41:31.480
Usually?

41:32.713 --> 41:34.350
I'm confused.

41:35.413 --> 41:38.513
Why would you hire me if
you knew who my mother was?

41:40.147 --> 41:42.608
The question isn't why I hired you.

41:43.447 --> 41:46.312
It's why you'd want to work
for the man who got her killed?

41:46.313 --> 41:54.313
♪♪♪

